args: Please note that this story contains spoilers\nfor the ＂The Accursed Archives＂ and\n＂Stirring Shadows＂ events.
We are Chaos. Our quietus is our genesis.\nWe reign in twilight; the dark nightmare\nof a stillborn sun.

We manifest the Ancient One's Emissary.
We are multifarious. Multifarious forms.
Multifarious names. Multifaaaaar...
Mul...tiiiii...faaaaar...
Once, not that long ago, I lived through\na terrifying, painful experience where\neveryone was turned into books.
But some really brave people saved me,\nso I'm okay now.
I don't need to be scared anymore.\nEveryone's going to be okay.
Do you truly believe that?\nDo you truly think the nightmare over?
Wh-who are you?! What are you saying?!
I am you, and you are me.\nWe am thee, and thou art Us.
You are chaos. We, the black and white.\nA continuance of the faceless one.\nAn oblivious infant, ever somnolent.
But the time of awakening is nigh.

Dear Mom and Dad,
After the terrifying incident where all
those poor people turned into books,
I settled in the village of Kyril.

Sadly, the person who cared for me
after you left also died, so I came to
the village to find a distant relative.
But when I arrived, I learned they,
too, had left this world.
But now the villagers themselves are\ncaring for me. It's mostly a good life,\nalthough I still have nightmares.
Why do I keep having such\nterrible dreams?
Oh, it's a cat! Are you lost, little kitty?
Just a stray, huh? Do you maybe\nwant to come home with me?
Then it's agreed. Come along, Ulthar!
That's your new name. I just thought of it.\n...Er, do you like it?
Hee hee! Oh, good. Then let's go!
Hee! That tickles! Oh, Ulthar, I haven't\nhad this much fun in a long time.
I've been alone for a long time.\nI live in my relative's house,\nbut they aren't here anymore.
Will you stay with me? I couldn't stand it\nif you left me alone like they did.
Thank you, Ulthar. Oh, and you can sleep\nin my bed tonight if you want.
Supplicate yourself, feline.\nPresent your life unto Us.
Unblemished feral life. Fleeting beast.\nNeck rent asunder. Life drunk dry.\nYour broken capitulum a sacrifice.
Offer yourself unto the Ancient One.
*pant* *pant* W-was that a dream...?\nOf course it was. It must have been.
I'd never do something like that.\nI'd never hurt little Ulthar.
No! No no no no no no...
Y-you're dead. So it...wasn't a dream?\nNo! No no no! I didn't kill you! I didn't!
